
    HOWTO: cross-compile for w32

1) Install mingw32. Some examples:

Arch linux:
* mingw32-gcc
* mingw32-w32api

FreeBSD:
* mingw32-gcc
* mingw32-bin-msvcrt

2) Begin by compiling the prerequisites. For example:

cd curl-$release; mkdir tmp; cd tmp
CFLAGS="-Os -pipe -march=i686" ../configure --host=i486-mingw32  --prefix=`pwd`/dist --without-ssl --without-ipv6 --without-random --disable-ldap && make install-strip

Repeat for all prerequisites.

3) Edit w32/make-w32.sh as needed. Fix the paths to prerequisites etc.

4) Run "./make-w32.sh && make". To build a dist archive from the compiled
files, try "./make-w32.sh -p". Note that you will need 7z (by default).


